City of Tuscaloosa lowers number of missing persons to 80
AL.com By on May 03, 2011 at 8:57 PM, updated
TUSCALOOSA, Alabama -- The city says the number of missing people in Tuscaloosa has dropped to 80. The number had ranged as high as 340 on Monday.
The city today also said the order to boil water before drinking had been lifted.
The changes were announced in the city's social media accounts via Twitter and Facebook.
To submit a missing person in Tuscaloosa or report that you are OK, visit Seek and Find.